^ Allan, Maxam; Walter, Gilbert (1980). "Sequencing end-labeled DNA with base-specific chemical cleavages". Methods in Enzymology. 65 (1): 499–560. PMID 6246368. doi:10.1016/S0076-6879(80)65059-9. 
^ Maxam, A.; Gilbert, W. (1977). "A new method for sequencing DNA". Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America. 74 (2): 560–564. Bibcode:1977PNAS...74..560M. PMC 392330 . PMID 265521. doi:10.1073/pnas.74.2.560. 
^ Hall, Stephen S. (1987). Invisible Frontiers: The Race to Synthesize a Human Gene. Atlantic Monthly Press. 
^ Gilbert, Walter (February 9, 1978). "Why genes in pieces". Nature. 271 (5645): 501. Bibcode:1978Natur.271..501G. PMID 622185. doi:10.1038/271501a0. 
^ Gilbert, W. (1986). "Origin of life: The RNA world". Nature. 319 (6055): 618–618. Bibcode:1986Natur.319..618G. doi:10.1038/319618a0. 
^ Brownlee, George G. (2015). "Frederick Sanger CBE CH OM. 13 August 1918 — 19 November 2013". Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal Society. Royal Society publishing. 61: 437–466. ISSN 0080-4606. doi:10.1098/rsbm.2015.0013. 
